## Use case

I have an array of objects with unique properties (name, id, URL, etc...).  I frequently need to find the object by the value of this property.
## Example

``` js
var data = [
  { name: 'a', ... },
  { name: 'b', ... },
  { name: 'c', ... }
];
var lookup = _.toLookup(data, 'name'); // (or a callback)
assert(lookup.a === data[0]);
```
## Questions

If there are duplicate keys, should it throw, use the last value, or use the first value?
## Sample implementation

``` js
function toLookup(arr, selector) {
    if (typeof selector === "string") {
        var property = selector;
        selector = function (obj) { return obj[property]; };
    }
    var retVal = {};
    for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        retVal[selector(arr[i])] = arr[i];
    }
    return retVal;
}
```

